flow_state|physical_rhythm_creative_movement_deep_focus_social_exchange|balanced|physical_rhythm|creative_movement|deep_focus|social_exchange|Why pace, ideas, and focus all matter|This pattern works as a flexible set of conditions, with Physical Rhythm lightly first. Creative Movement may open the route, Deep Focus may give it weight, and Social Exchange may test it.|It may show up because different tasks ask for different entries. Some need movement, some need a fresh angle, some need quiet attention, and some need a response from another person.|It protects adaptable progress. The trade-off is that conversation may be treated as a later check even when earlier response would make the work clearer.|active|flow_state::physical_rhythm_creative_movement_deep_focus_social_exchange::balanced
flow_state|physical_rhythm_creative_movement_social_exchange_deep_focus|concentrated|physical_rhythm|creative_movement|social_exchange|deep_focus|Why active ideas need a finish point|This pattern works by using movement and ideas to create early energy, then using exchange to test what is emerging. Deep Focus may need deliberate use when the result needs care, finish, or refinement.|It may show up because the person trusts work that becomes clearer through action, variation, and response. A static start may feel less reliable than doing a rough version and seeing what changes.|It protects momentum, range, and quick testing. The trade-off is that careful focus can arrive late if the work keeps moving before it settles.|active|flow_state::physical_rhythm_creative_movement_social_exchange_deep_focus::concentrated
flow_state|physical_rhythm_creative_movement_social_exchange_deep_focus|paired|physical_rhythm|creative_movement|social_exchange|deep_focus|Why rhythm needs variation|This pattern works through a close link between practical rhythm and fresh angles. Physical Rhythm gives the work momentum, while Creative Movement keeps that momentum responsive and less automatic.|It may show up because the person often finds a better route by doing, adjusting, making, moving, or changing pace. Ideas help the action stay flexible rather than repetitive.|It protects active range. The trade-off is that Social Exchange and Deep Focus may need deliberate space so the idea is tested, refined, and completed.|active|flow_state::physical_rhythm_creative_movement_social_exchange_deep_focus::paired
flow_state|physical_rhythm_creative_movement_social_exchange_deep_focus|graduated|physical_rhythm|creative_movement|social_exchange|deep_focus|Why the route tests before it refines|This pattern works through a clear order. Physical Rhythm starts momentum, Creative Movement adds variation, Social Exchange tests the idea, and Deep Focus gives the final work substance.|It may show up because practical activity and fresh angles help each other before heavy analysis is useful. Response then shows what is clear before focus is needed to finish.|It protects active experimentation that can become visible quickly. The trade-off is that careful refinement may be delayed until the work already has social or practical momentum.|active|flow_state::physical_rhythm_creative_movement_social_exchange_deep_focus::graduated
